  <constraints>
    <constraint source="R5 CLAUDE.md §3.5 / §10 / ADR-013 §3.5 Zone B boundary">R5 is a **Zone B consumer** of the Insights HTTP contract. Tool MUST call `POST /api/insights/assistant/query` via HTTP. MUST NOT inject `IInsightsAi`, `InsightsOrchestrator`, `AssistantToolCallHandler`, `InsightsIntentClassifier`, `IInsightsPlaybookExecutionCache`, `IRagService` Insights-specific extensions, or any other type from `src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Services/Ai/Insights/` (or `Models/Insights/`) directly. The endpoint co-locates in the same BFF process — same-process HTTP is the canonical pattern for Zone B consumption and is intentional. Boundary verified by grep of the new tool class for `using ...Services.Ai.Insights` / `Models.Insights` namespaces.</constraint>
    <constraint source="R5 CLAUDE.md §3.1 / reuse mandate">MUST register on the EXISTING `SprkChatAgent` via the EXISTING `SprkChatAgentFactory.ResolveTools` mechanism (the same site that wires `AnalysisExecutionTools`, `DocumentSearchTools`, `WorkingDocumentTools`, and `InvokeSummarizePlaybookTool` from task 015 through `AIFunctionFactory.Create`). MUST NOT introduce a parallel chat agent, a parallel tool registration framework, a parallel `IChatAgent` interface, or a parallel `AIFunction`-emitting abstraction.</constraint>
    <constraint source="ADR-013">All AI orchestration in BFF; agents are created exclusively via `SprkChatAgentFactory`; the middleware stack (cost control, content safety, telemetry, service routing) MUST wrap tool execution by virtue of using the existing factory. R5 is Zone A in the chat-tool-handler space (BFF service surface) AND Zone B in the Insights contract space — the tool's job is to bridge these zones cleanly.</constraint>
    <constraint source="ADR-010 + R5 §3.3">DI minimalism — tool class is constructed inside `SprkChatAgentFactory.ResolveTools` per the AIPL-053 / AnalysisExecutionTools precedent (preferred path — zero new DI registration); if a typed `HttpClient` is required, register it inside the EXISTING `AnalysisServicesModule.cs` feature module via `services.AddHttpClient<InsightsQueryToolHandler>(...)` (single line, inside the feature module — NOT in `Program.cs`). ZERO new top-level `services.AddXxx()` lines in `Program.cs`.</constraint>
    <constraint source="ADR-018 (R5 §3.2)">R5 introduces NO new feature flags. Tool registers unconditionally inside the existing capability-gated tool block. Kill-switch coverage inherits via `NullSprkChatAgentFactory` when Chat capability is disabled. The Insights endpoint enforces its own kill-switches (`Compound:AI:Enabled`, `Insights:Rag:Enabled`, `Insights:IntentClassifier:Enabled`) — this tool surfaces their 503 responses to the renderer for per-code UX.</constraint>
    <constraint source="ADR-029 / R5 CLAUDE.md §3.6">BFF publish-size verification — run `dotnet publish -c Release src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/ -o deploy/api-publish/`, measure compressed output, report absolute size + delta vs prior baseline in task notes. Ceiling ≤60 MB compressed; R5 budget ≤+1 MB cumulative (target +0.5 MB). Expected delta is small (one new tool class + tool-resolution block + at most one `AddHttpClient` line) — target ≤+0.1 MB.</constraint>
    <constraint source="spec NFR-12 (tool routing discipline)">Tool description text is load-bearing for correct LLM tool-routing. Description MUST be: "Answer matter/project/invoice-scoped analytical questions about entities" (per plan.md D2-14 + spec NFR-12). MUST explicitly differentiate from `InvokeSummarizePlaybook` (file-scoped, session-scoped) per UR-01 mitigation. Description text is curated explicitly to prevent ambiguous routing. Tool name registered via `AIFunctionFactory.Create` is `insights.query` exactly.</constraint>
    <constraint source="spec FR-12 (Insights tool registration)">Tool MUST be registered; LLM MUST be able to call it for natural-language matter/project/invoice queries; slash command path (task 019) MUST bypass the BFF classifier via `forceMode` parameter.</constraint>
    <constraint source="spec FR-16 (12 error codes)">Tool MUST surface ALL 12 contract error codes (integration brief §5.1) to the renderer with stable `errorCode` extension preserved + `correlationId` preserved. Errors NEVER include document content, prompt text, LLM raw output, or stack traces. 503 `ai.intent-classification.disabled` triggers an Assistant-side retry with `forceMode` (if intent signal available); 500 triggers a single retry with 1s backoff. Per-code UX is the renderer's job (task 026) — this task surfaces the structured error.</constraint>
    <constraint source="spec FR-17 / SC-16 (correlation-id propagation)">Tool MUST generate a unique `x-correlation-id` per Assistant turn and propagate it as an HTTP request header on every outbound call. The same correlation ID MUST appear in chat-agent telemetry (e.g., `Activity` span tag or telemetry event property) per ADR-019 so App Insights / Kusto end-to-end correlation works. Verified by an integration log inspection at Step 8.</constraint>
    <constraint source="spec FR-12 / SC-17 (forceMode semantics)">Tool accepts `forceMode: string?` parameter. Slash command path (task 019 `/ask-insights playbook ...` / `/ask-insights rag ...`) sets it explicitly. LLM tool-call path leaves it absent (BFF classifier decides). Tool MUST forward whatever value the caller provides (or omit when null) — does NOT default `forceMode` itself. Invalid values surface as the contract's 400 `forceMode.invalid` error from the BFF.</constraint>
    <constraint source="ADR-028 (R5 §10)">No token snapshots — the tool runs inside the existing agent session whose host context already carries a fresh OBO token per `SprkChatAgentFactory`. Forward `HttpContext.Request.Headers.Authorization` (or use the existing `@spaarke/auth`-equivalent server-side helper) per request — do NOT snapshot or pass tokens into the tool class constructor.</constraint>
    <constraint source="ADR-016 (rate limiting honoring)">Tool MUST honor `Retry-After` on 429 responses (`ai-context` policy; 60/min/oid aggregate across `/ask` + `/search` + `/assistant/query`). On 429, surface the rate-limit error structurally to the renderer; do NOT auto-retry inside the tool.</constraint>
    <constraint source="ADR-019 (ProblemDetails parsing)">Tool MUST parse error responses as `application/problem+json` per ADR-019. Extract `errorCode` (stable extension), `correlationId`, `status`, `title`, `detail`. Preserve these in the structured tool-error so the renderer (task 026) can map per-code UX from integration brief §5.1 column 4.</constraint>
    <constraint source="CLAUDE.md §10 / bff-extensions §F test obligation">PRs modifying `src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Services/` MUST add/update tests in `tests/unit/Sprk.Bff.Api.Tests/`. Tool wrapper class + tool-registration site changes require accompanying tests (mock `HttpMessageHandler` for the typed client; assert request shape, header propagation, response parsing, error mapping).</constraint>
    <constraint source="project (AIPU2-061 routing)">Tool name `insights.query` MUST be discoverable by `CapabilityRouter` — added to the appropriate playbook capability's `ToolNames` allow-list (e.g., new `PlaybookCapabilities.InsightsQuery` constant if no existing fit; prefer reuse). Verify routing through both the keyword (Layer 1) and LLM (Layer 2) layers selects this tool for natural-language matter/project/invoice analytical prompts.</constraint>
    <constraint source="contract v1.0 §3 (subject format)">Tool accepts `subject` parameter as a string in the format `<scheme>:<guid>` where scheme is `matter` / `project` / `invoice`. Tool does NOT validate the subject format itself — the BFF returns 400 `subject.invalid` for malformed values, surfaced via the error path. Subject RESOLUTION from chat context is task 025's job; this task accepts whatever subject the caller (LLM or slash command) provides.</constraint>
    <constraint source="contract v1.0 §3.1 (query length)">Tool accepts `query` parameter (required, 1..500 chars). Tool does NOT pre-truncate or pre-validate length; the BFF returns 400 `query.required` for empty/whitespace and rejects oversized requests via ProblemDetails — surfaced via the error path.</constraint>
    <constraint source="contract v1.1 forward-compat">Phase 1.5 contract is forward-compatible. New optional response fields (e.g., v1.1 `citations[].href` per task 027) that this tool ignores will be silently accepted in Phase 2. Tool response forwarding MUST NOT strip unknown fields — use loose JSON deserialization (e.g., `JsonElement` passthrough or DTO with `[JsonExtensionData]`) for the structured-result envelope.</constraint>
  </constraints>

