    <patterns>
      <pattern name="AIFunctionFactory.Create tool wiring (canonical reference)" location="src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Services/Ai/Chat/Tools/AnalysisExecutionTools.cs">
        Tool class is a `public sealed class` constructed inside
        `SprkChatAgentFactory.ResolveTools` (NOT registered in DI per ADR-010 + AIPL-053).
        Exposes a `public IEnumerable&lt;AIFunction&gt; GetTools()` method that yields
        `AIFunctionFactory.Create(methodReference, name: "insights.query", description: "Answer matter/project/invoice-scoped analytical questions about entities")`.
        The `[Description("...")]` attribute on the method + parameters is load-bearing
        for LLM tool-schema generation. Mirror this exactly for
        `InsightsQueryToolHandler`.
      </pattern>
      <pattern name="Capability-gated tool resolution block" location="src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Services/Ai/Chat/SprkChatAgentFactory.cs (lines 807–834 for AnalysisExecutionTools)">
        Tool instantiation lives inside `ResolveTools` wrapped in `try/catch` with
        `attempted++ / resolved++ / failedTools.Add(...)` bookkeeping per AIPU2-063
        per-tool error isolation. Gate behind the chosen Insights playbook capability
        (e.g., `capabilities.Contains(PlaybookCapabilities.InsightsQuery)`). The factory
        resolves required services (typed `HttpClient`, logger, telemetry) from
        `scopedProvider`. Mirror the same shape used in task 015's
        `InvokeSummarizePlaybookTool` block.
      </pattern>
      <pattern name="Zone B HTTP consumption via IHttpClientFactory typed client" location="(repository-wide — typed `HttpClient` precedent)">
        Register the typed client inside `AnalysisServicesModule.cs`:
        `services.AddHttpClient&lt;InsightsQueryToolHandler&gt;(client =&gt; { client.BaseAddress = new Uri(bffBaseAddress); client.DefaultRequestHeaders.Accept.Add(new MediaTypeWithQualityHeaderValue("application/json")); });`
        Configure timeout to a sensible upper bound (e.g., 60s — Insights playbook path
        latency p95 ~2s but RAG path can spike). Forward bearer token per request from
        `HttpContext` (DO NOT snapshot per ADR-028). Generate `x-correlation-id` per
        call using `Activity.Current?.Id ?? Guid.NewGuid().ToString("N")`.
      </pattern>
      <pattern name="ProblemDetails error parsing (ADR-019)" location="(repository-wide — ProblemDetails parsing precedent)">
        Parse error responses as `application/problem+json`. Use
        `JsonSerializer.Deserialize&lt;ProblemDetails&gt;(content)` (or a custom record
        with `errorCode` + `correlationId` extensions). Preserve all 12 contract error
        codes from integration brief §5.1 (`query.required`, `subject.required`,
        `subject.invalid`, `forceMode.invalid`, `conversationContext.invalid`,
        `ai.insights.disabled`, `ai.rag.disabled`, `ai.intent-classification.disabled`,
        `ai.assistant-default-playbook.unconfigured`,
        `INSIGHTS_ASSISTANT_INTERNAL_ERROR`, plus 401 + 429 generic).
      </pattern>
      <pattern name="AIPU2-061 CapabilityRouter per-turn tool-injection" location="src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Services/Ai/Capabilities/CapabilityRouter.cs">
        The Layer 1 keyword classifier + Layer 2 LLM classifier select a subset of
        tools per turn. The capability manifest entries' `ToolNames` lists determine
        which tools are discoverable. Register `insights.query` in the appropriate
        playbook capability's `ToolNames` allow-list (or add a new capability key —
        prefer reuse).
      </pattern>
      <pattern name="Loose response deserialization for forward-compat" location="(integration brief §4 + v1.1 forward-compat)">
        Use `JsonElement` or `[JsonExtensionData]` for unknown fields on the response
        DTO so v1.1 additions (`citations[].href`, SSE-related fields) pass through to
        the renderer (task 026) without code changes here.
      </pattern>
      <pattern name="Sibling tool registration block (task 015 — InvokeSummarizePlaybookTool)" location="src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Services/Ai/Chat/SprkChatAgentFactory.cs (added by task 015)">
        Mirror the exact shape used by task 015 — same try/catch error-isolation
        scaffolding, same `attempted++ / resolved++ / failedTools.Add(...)` discipline,
        same capability-gated `if (capabilities.Contains(...))` guard. Place this block
        adjacent to task 015's block for visual grouping.
      </pattern>
    </patterns>
  </knowledge>

  <context>
    <background>
      R5 ships a chat-driven "Summarize a Document" vertical slice AND the Insights tool
      integration (`insights.query`) through the SpaarkeAi three-pane shell. The R5 chat
      agent becomes the **Spaarke Assistant** in operational form — hosting two AI tool
      capabilities (Summarize from task 015 + Insights from this task) alongside the
      existing ad-hoc grounded-LLM mode.

      The Insights Engine R2 Wave E shipped `POST /api/insights/assistant/query` (BFF
      task 042) specifically as the R5 consumption surface — a single endpoint that
      internally routes between a playbook path (predictive structured answer) and a
      RAG path (citation-grounded prose) via an LLM intent classifier (or via the
      Assistant-supplied `forceMode` override). The contract is binding at v1.0
      (`notes/insights-engine-assistant-integration-brief.md`); v1.1 (SSE + clickable
      citations) is the Wave F deliverable, ship-time-coordinated with R5 Phase 2 per
      `notes/insights-r2-coordination.md`.

      Tool-routing disambiguation between `insights.query` and `InvokeSummarizePlaybook`
      (task 015) is the load-bearing UR-01 risk — the LLM Layer 2 classifier must pick
      the right tool for natural-language prompts. The mitigation is tool-description-
      quality discipline (spec NFR-12 + plan.md High-Risk Items table). This task's
      description text — "Answer matter/project/invoice-scoped analytical questions
      about entities" — is the entity-scoped / knowledge-scoped half of the
      mitigation; task 015's description is the file-scoped / session-scoped half.

      This is the FIRST task of P2-G6 (Insights tool integration suite). Subsequent
      tasks: 025 (subject resolution + HTTP client refinement), 026 (two-path response
      renderer `InsightsResponseRenderer`), 027 (clickable citations — v1.1 forward),
      028 (confidence floor badge). This task ships the BFF-side tool handler that
      tasks 025–028 build atop on the frontend.

      Zone B boundary discipline: R5 CLAUDE.md §3.5 and §10 explicitly call out that
      R5 NEVER injects Insights internals. The endpoint co-locates in the same BFF
      process today, but the boundary is binding per refined ADR-013 §3.5. Same-
      process HTTP is the canonical Zone B consumption pattern.

      This task adds NO new top-level `Program.cs` lines, NO new feature flags
      (kill-switch coverage inherits from `NullSprkChatAgentFactory` + the Insights
      endpoint's own kill-switches), and NO new chat-agent or tool framework. It does
      add ONE `services.AddHttpClient&lt;InsightsQueryToolHandler&gt;(...)` line inside
      `AnalysisServicesModule.cs` to register the typed client (preferred pattern per
      `IHttpClientFactory` best practice).
    </background>
