  <steps>
    <step order="0" name="Context Check + RIGOR LEVEL declaration">
      Check context usage. If &gt; 70%, run `context-handoff` and request `/compact`.
      Declare RIGOR LEVEL explicitly per CLAUDE.md §8:

      ```
      🔒 RIGOR LEVEL: FULL
      📋 REASON: BFF code change in chat-agent tool registration site + new tool class
                 + Zone B HTTP consumption (Insights contract) + AI infrastructure +
                 AIPU2-061 capability router coupling. Tags: bff + chat-agent +
                 tool-registration + insights + ai. Qualifies for FULL per task-execute
                 decision tree.
      📖 PROTOCOL STEPS TO EXECUTE: Steps 0–10 with Step 9.5 quality gates.
      Proceeding with Step 0...
      ```
    </step>
    <step order="1" name="Review Progress">
      Read `tasks/TASK-INDEX.md`. Confirm task 024 status is 🔲, dependency 023 is ✅
      (BLOCKING gate — if 023 is 🔲, STOP and report; do not begin tool integration
      without contract sign-off), parallel-safe = true (P2-G6), siblings 025/026/027/
      028. Read `current-task.md` to verify no R5 task is in flight conflicting with
      this site. Confirm task 015 status (sibling — `InvokeSummarizePlaybookTool`
      description-coordination concern). Read project README for project status.
    </step>
    <step order="2" name="Gather Resources">
      Read every file in &lt;inputs&gt; and &lt;knowledge&gt;. Specifically:
      (a) Read `notes/insights-engine-assistant-integration-brief.md` in full — this
          is the BINDING contract v1.0. Internalize §3 (request schema), §4 (response
          schema both paths), §5 (12 error codes + per-code recommended action), §10
          (coordination protocol).
      (b) Read `notes/insights-engine-contract-v1.1-request.md` §0a Negotiation
          Outcome — confirm v1.1 forward-compat scope (SSE + clickable citations) is
          OUT of this task's scope (task 027 covers v1.1 citations; SSE is Wave F
          coordination).
      (c) Read `SprkChatAgentFactory.ResolveTools` (lines 540–1040) to internalize the
          tool-registration block pattern + AIPU2-063 error-isolation discipline.
      (d) Read `AnalysisExecutionTools.cs` (canonical tool-class shape) and
          `AnalysisQueryTools.cs` (canonical pattern when constructor takes a service).
      (e) Read task 015's POML to confirm the InvokeSummarizePlaybookTool description
          text + capability constant chosen (drives NFR-12 differentiation discipline).
      (f) Read task 023's POML to confirm the contract sign-off decisions D1–D6
          (any decisions affect this task's surface — e.g., D1 SSE deferral confirms
          single-shot HTTP, D2 forceMode-without-playbookHint defaults to BFF config,
          D4 citation display name fallback shape).
      (g) Read ADR-013 (§3.5 Zone B boundary), ADR-010, ADR-018, ADR-019, ADR-028 in
          full.
      (h) Read `InsightsAssistantEndpoint.cs` + `InsightsAssistantQueryRequest.cs`
          ONLY for reference — do NOT import them in the new tool class (Zone B
          boundary; same-process HTTP only).
      (i) Read `bff-extensions.md` §F (test obligation) + §F.1 (asymmetric-registration
          anti-pattern) — verify unconditional registration discipline.
    </step>
    <step order="3" name="Tool description authoring (NFR-12 + UR-01 mitigation)">
      The description text is the single most load-bearing artifact of this task per
      NFR-12. The spec MANDATES the wording: "Answer matter/project/invoice-scoped
      analytical questions about entities" (spec NFR-12 + plan.md D2-14). This is the
      baseline. Author + record in task notes a fuller parameter-aware description for
      `AIFunctionFactory.Create`:

      Mandatory baseline: "Answer matter/project/invoice-scoped analytical questions
      about entities. Use for questions about a specific matter, project, or invoice
      (predicted cost, key dates, closing conditions, outstanding amounts, etc.). Do
      NOT use for summarizing files uploaded to the current chat session (use
      InvokeSummarizePlaybook for that)."

      Author parameter-level `[Description(...)]` attributes for `query`, `subject`,
      and `forceMode`:
      - `query`: "The user's natural-language question (1..500 chars). Required."
      - `subject`: "The scope entity in the format '&lt;scheme&gt;:&lt;guid&gt;' where
        scheme is 'matter', 'project', or 'invoice'. Resolved from the active chat
        host context. Required."
      - `forceMode`: "Optional. Set to 'playbook' or 'rag' when invoking via an
        explicit slash command. Omit for natural-language tool-calls — the BFF
        intent classifier will route automatically."

      Record the final description text (method-level + each parameter-level) in
      task notes `notes/task-024-evidence.md` for cross-reference with task 015's
      description (NFR-12 audit pair).

      Also: identify the playbook capability under which to gate the tool. Read
      `PlaybookCapabilities` constants in the existing factory; prefer to reuse an
      existing Insights-related capability if one exists; otherwise add a new constant
      `PlaybookCapabilities.InsightsQuery`. Decide between (a) typed `HttpClient`
      injected via `IHttpClientFactory` registered in `AnalysisServicesModule.cs`
      (preferred), or (b) `HttpClient` passed in directly from the factory's scoped
      provider. Record decision.
    </step>
    <step order="4" name="Create `InsightsQueryToolHandler` class">
      Create
      `src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Services/Ai/Chat/Tools/InsightsQueryToolHandler.cs`
      following the canonical `AnalysisExecutionTools` shape:
      - `public sealed class InsightsQueryToolHandler`
      - Constructor: takes `HttpClient httpClient` (typed client, scoped),
        `ILogger&lt;InsightsQueryToolHandler&gt; logger`, optional `HttpContext` for
        OBO bearer-token forwarding per ADR-028 (NOT a token snapshot — pass the
        context through and read the auth header per call).
      - Method:
        `public async Task&lt;string&gt; InsightsQueryAsync(string query, string subject, string? forceMode, CancellationToken ct)`
        decorated with `[Description("Answer matter/project/invoice-scoped analytical questions about entities. ...")]`
      - Parameter attributes: `[Description("...")]` on each parameter per Step 3.
      - Implementation:
        1. Construct request DTO `{ query, subject, forceMode, conversationContext: null }`
           per integration brief §3 (request schema). Use a private record matching
           the contract — does NOT import `InsightsAssistantQueryRequest` (Zone B
           boundary).
        2. Generate `x-correlation-id`:
           `var correlationId = Activity.Current?.Id ?? Guid.NewGuid().ToString("N");`
           Add as request header. Log + emit as telemetry tag for FR-17 / SC-16.
        3. Forward OBO bearer token from `HttpContext.Request.Headers.Authorization`
           to the outbound request (set `Authorization` header on the HttpRequestMessage).
        4. POST to `/api/insights/assistant/query` (relative to typed client's
           configured BaseAddress).
        5. Parse response:
           - On 200 OK: deserialize loosely (use `JsonElement` for `structuredResult`
             + `[JsonExtensionData]` on the outer DTO for v1.1 forward-compat). Return
             the JSON string to the agent's conversation context.
           - On non-2xx with `application/problem+json`: parse `ProblemDetails` per
             ADR-019; extract `errorCode`, `correlationId`, `status`, `title`,
             `detail`; throw a structured `InsightsToolException` (private exception
             type in the same file or a small companion file) preserving all four
             fields. The middleware stack / agent SSE pipe converts this into the
             tool-error envelope surfaced to the renderer (task 026).
           - On 401 with no `errorCode`: surface as `InsightsToolException` with
             `errorCode = "auth.401"` (synthetic — distinct from contract codes).
           - On 429: extract `Retry-After` header; surface as `InsightsToolException`
             with `errorCode = "rate-limit.429"` + retry-after value.
        6. Telemetry: emit `Activity` span tags for `insights.path` (from response
           header `X-Insights-Path` when present), `insights.elapsedMs`,
           `insights.cacheHit`, `correlationId` per FR-17 / FR-18.
      - `public IEnumerable&lt;AIFunction&gt; GetTools()` yielding
        `AIFunctionFactory.Create(InsightsQueryAsync, name: "insights.query", description: "...")`.
      Mirror the XML doc-comment density of `AnalysisExecutionTools.cs`.

      Verify Zone B boundary by grep: the new file MUST NOT contain
      `using Sprk.Bff.Api.Services.Ai.Insights` or
      `using Sprk.Bff.Api.Models.Insights` namespaces. Use the local private request
      record + loose response DTO with `JsonElement` instead.
    </step>
    <step order="5" name="Register typed HttpClient inside `AnalysisServicesModule.cs`">
      Inside the EXISTING `AnalysisServicesModule.cs` feature module (NOT in
      `Program.cs` per ADR-010 + R5 §3.3), add a single `services.AddHttpClient&lt;...&gt;`
      line for the tool's typed client:

      ```csharp
      // --- InsightsQueryToolHandler typed client (R5 D2-14) ---
      // Zone B HTTP consumption of the Insights /assistant/query endpoint.
      services.AddHttpClient&lt;InsightsQueryToolHandler&gt;(client =&gt;
      {
          var bffBaseAddress = configuration["Bff:BaseAddress"]
              ?? "https://localhost:7001"; // local dev fallback
          client.BaseAddress = new Uri(bffBaseAddress);
          client.Timeout = TimeSpan.FromSeconds(60);
          client.DefaultRequestHeaders.Accept.Add(
              new MediaTypeWithQualityHeaderValue("application/json"));
      });
      ```

      Verify the config key `Bff:BaseAddress` resolves correctly across environments
      (Spaarke Dev / Local). If a different key is conventional in the repo (e.g.,
      `ApiBaseAddress`), use the existing convention — search for prior typed-client
      registrations in `AnalysisServicesModule.cs` and adjacent modules. Document the
      chosen config key in task notes.

      ZERO new top-level `Program.cs` lines per ADR-010.
    </step>
    <step order="6" name="Wire tool into `SprkChatAgentFactory.ResolveTools`">
      Extend `SprkChatAgentFactory.ResolveTools` with a new capability-gated block,
      placed adjacent to task 015's `InvokeSummarizePlaybookTool` block. Pattern
      (mirror existing tool-resolution blocks + task 015 exactly):

      ```csharp
      // --- InsightsQueryToolHandler (R5 D2-14) ---
      // Gated behind the InsightsQuery capability.
      // Consumes POST /api/insights/assistant/query (Insights endpoint, Zone B).
      if (capabilities.Contains(PlaybookCapabilities.InsightsQuery))
      {
          attempted++;
          try
          {
              var insightsQueryTool = scopedProvider.GetRequiredService&lt;InsightsQueryToolHandler&gt;();
              tools.AddRange(insightsQueryTool.GetTools());
              resolved++;
          }
          catch (Exception ex)
          {
              _logger.LogWarning(ex, "Failed to resolve InsightsQueryToolHandler — skipping");
              failedTools.Add(nameof(InsightsQueryToolHandler));
          }
      }
      ```

      The tool is resolved from `scopedProvider` because the typed `HttpClient` is
      registered via `AddHttpClient&lt;InsightsQueryToolHandler&gt;` (which transitively
      registers the handler as transient/scoped). If a new capability constant is
      needed, add it inside `PlaybookCapabilities` static class. ZERO new
      `Program.cs` lines per ADR-010.
    </step>
    <step order="7" name="Update capability manifest + `ToolNames` allow-list (AIPU2-061)">
      Update the appropriate capability manifest entry (or capability constants file)
      so `insights.query` appears in `ToolNames` for the chosen capability
      (`InsightsQuery`). This makes the tool discoverable by
      `CapabilityRouter.RouteAsync` and selectable for per-turn injection when the
      user's prompt classifies as entity-scoped analytical-question intent. Verify via
      the `CapabilityValidator` flow (per AIPU2-061 line 1088+ in
      `SprkChatAgentFactory.cs`).
    </step>
    <step order="8" name="Author tests (delegation, Zone B boundary, error mapping, forceMode, correlation-id)">
      Add a unit test in
      `tests/unit/Sprk.Bff.Api.Tests/Services/Ai/Chat/Tools/InsightsQueryToolHandlerTests.cs`:
      - **Test 1 (success — playbook path)**: Mock `HttpMessageHandler` returns 200
        OK with the integration brief §4.6 playbook sample. Assert
        `InsightsQueryAsync("predicted cost?", "matter:...", "playbook", ct)` POSTs
        to `/api/insights/assistant/query` with request body
        `{ query, subject, forceMode: "playbook", conversationContext: null }`,
        forwards bearer token, sets `x-correlation-id` header. Assert response is
        returned with `path: "playbook"` preserved.
      - **Test 2 (success — RAG path)**: Mock returns 200 OK with integration brief
        §4.6 RAG sample. Assert `forceMode` omitted from request when null. Assert
        response `path: "rag"` preserved.
      - **Test 3 (forceMode semantics)**: `forceMode: null` → field omitted /
        serialized as null per contract; `forceMode: "playbook"` → forwarded;
        `forceMode: "rag"` → forwarded; `forceMode: "garbage"` → forwarded (BFF
        returns 400 `forceMode.invalid` — tool does NOT pre-validate).
      - **Test 4 (error mapping — 12 codes)**: For each of the 12 contract error
        codes (integration brief §5.1), mock the response and assert the tool throws
        `InsightsToolException` preserving `errorCode`, `correlationId`, `status`,
        `title`, `detail`. Include: `query.required`, `subject.required`,
        `subject.invalid`, `forceMode.invalid`, `conversationContext.invalid`,
        `auth.401` (synthetic), `rate-limit.429` (synthetic with Retry-After),
        `ai.insights.disabled`, `ai.rag.disabled`,
        `ai.intent-classification.disabled`,
        `ai.assistant-default-playbook.unconfigured`,
        `INSIGHTS_ASSISTANT_INTERNAL_ERROR`.
      - **Test 5 (correlation-id propagation)**: Tool generates a unique
        `x-correlation-id` per call; same value emitted as telemetry tag /
        `Activity` baggage; recoverable from log output. Assert via mocked logger
        + captured `HttpRequestMessage`.
      - **Test 6 (Zone B boundary)**: Programmatic grep against the new tool class
        file — assert no `using Sprk.Bff.Api.Services.Ai.Insights` or `Models.Insights`
        appears. Implement as a unit test reading the source file content (or use a
        repo-level convention test if one exists).
      - **Test 7 (v1.1 forward-compat)**: Mock returns 200 with extra unknown fields
        (e.g., `citations[0].href = "..."`, top-level `streaming: true`). Tool
        passes them through unchanged.
      - **Test 8 (no token snapshot)**: Assert that the tool reads
        `HttpContext.Request.Headers.Authorization` per call (NOT in constructor).
        Simulated case: first call carries token A, second call carries token B
        (token rotated mid-session) — tool forwards the correct token each call.

      Add a routing test in
      `tests/unit/Sprk.Bff.Api.Tests/Services/Ai/Chat/SprkChatAgentFactoryTests.cs`
      (or a new file) asserting: when `capabilities` contains
      `PlaybookCapabilities.InsightsQuery`, `insights.query` appears in the resolved
      `IReadOnlyList&lt;AIFunction&gt;`; when absent, it does NOT appear; when
      `routingResult` filters tools to a different capability, this tool is excluded
      per AIPU2-061.
    </step>
    <step order="9" name="Smoke test against Spaarke Dev BFF (acceptance criteria)">
      With BFF deployed to Spaarke Dev (or running locally with `Bff:BaseAddress`
      pointed to Spaarke Dev), exercise the chat agent end-to-end:

      Positive prompts (MUST tool-call `insights.query`):
      - "what will this matter cost to complete?" (set HostContext to test matter
        `da116923-d65a-f111-a825-3833c5d9bcb1`)
      - "what closing conditions are in this matter?"
      - "list outstanding invoices for this project" (HostContext project
        `27845394-8e5f-f111-a825-70a8a59455f4`)
      - "give me a status update on this invoice" (HostContext invoice
        `05c8ef8d-8e5f-f111-a825-70a8a59455f4`)

      Negative prompts (MUST NOT tool-call `insights.query`):
      - "summarize the attached document" (with files uploaded → should select
        `InvokeSummarizePlaybook` from task 015)
      - "give me a TL;DR of the files I uploaded"

      Slash command path:
      - `/ask-insights playbook ...` (task 019) → tool called with `forceMode:
        "playbook"`
      - `/ask-insights rag ...` (task 019) → tool called with `forceMode: "rag"`
      - Natural language `/ask-insights ...` without explicit mode → tool called with
        `forceMode` omitted

      Verifications:
      - At least 3 of 4 positive prompts route correctly to `insights.query`.
      - Negative prompts do NOT spuriously trigger `insights.query` (UR-01 mitigation).
      - `x-correlation-id` header is set on every outbound request (capture via BFF
        log inspection on Spaarke Dev). Same ID appears in App Insights / Kusto
        end-to-end trace.
      - Slash command path sets `forceMode` correctly; natural-language path omits it.
      - Sample error response (intentionally malformed subject) surfaces the contract
        error code (`subject.invalid`) via `InsightsToolException`.

      Capture all tool-call traces in task notes `notes/task-024-evidence.md`. If
      routing is incorrect, refine the description text (Step 3) and re-run.
    </step>
    <step order="9.5" name="Quality Gates (FULL rigor)">
      Run `code-review` skill against the new tool class +
      `SprkChatAgentFactory.ResolveTools` extension + `AnalysisServicesModule.cs`
      AddHttpClient line + test file(s). Run `adr-check` skill against the same;
      verify:
      - **ADR-013 §3.5 (Zone B boundary)**: tool calls Insights via HTTP; no
        `using ...Services.Ai.Insights` / `Models.Insights` imports. Verified by
        explicit grep at Step 8 Test 6 + reviewer inspection.
      - **ADR-010 (DI minimalism)**: zero new top-level `Program.cs` lines; single
        `AddHttpClient` inside feature module.
      - **ADR-018 (no new feature flag)**: kill-switch inherits via
        `NullSprkChatAgentFactory`; Insights endpoint enforces own kill-switches and
        their 503 responses surface to the renderer.
      - **ADR-019 (ProblemDetails parsing)**: error path preserves `errorCode` +
        `correlationId` + `status` + `title` + `detail`.
      - **ADR-028 (no token snapshot)**: token forwarded fresh per call from
        `HttpContext`; Test 8 confirms.
      - **ADR-016 (rate-limit honoring)**: 429 surfaced structurally; no in-tool
        auto-retry.

      All gates MUST pass before marking the task complete.

      Run BFF publish + size check:
      `dotnet publish -c Release src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/ -o deploy/api-publish/`
      Measure compressed output; record absolute size + delta vs prior baseline (per
      R5 CLAUDE.md §3.6). Expected delta is small (one new tool class +
      `AddHttpClient` line + one tool-resolution block) — target +0.0–0.1 MB.

      Verify no new HIGH-severity CVE:
      `dotnet list package --vulnerable --include-transitive`.
    </step>
    <step order="10" name="Document + Complete">
      Update task POML status to `complete`. Update `TASK-INDEX.md`: 024 🔲 → ✅.
      Reset `current-task.md` to the next pending P2-G6 task per CLAUDE.md §7 (likely
      025 or 026). Record in task notes (`notes/task-024-evidence.md`):
