  <acceptance-criteria>
    <criterion testable="true">`InsightsQueryToolHandler` is registered via the EXISTING `SprkChatAgentFactory.ResolveTools` mechanism (no new chat agent, no new tool framework, no new top-level DI lines). Confirmed by `SprkChatAgentFactoryTests` assertion that the tool appears in the resolved `IReadOnlyList&lt;AIFunction&gt;` when the gating capability is present.</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">Tool name registered via `AIFunctionFactory.Create` is exactly `insights.query` (lowercase, dot-separated). Confirmed by unit test asserting `AIFunction.Name == "insights.query"`.</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">Tool description scopes routing correctly per NFR-12 baseline: "Answer matter/project/invoice-scoped analytical questions about entities ..." with explicit differentiation from `InvokeSummarizePlaybook` (file-scoped / session-scoped). Final description text recorded in task notes; NFR-12 audit pair cross-reference to task 015's description confirms no semantic overlap.</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">Tool is visible in the agent's tool catalog (factory log line emits `resolved++` count including this tool; `ResolveTools` returns it). Confirmed by integration log inspection on Spaarke Dev.</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">LLM correctly tool-calls `insights.query` for at least 3 of 4 natural-language matter/project/invoice analytical test prompts (smoke test Step 9). Negative prompts (file-scoped Summarize prompts) do NOT spuriously trigger this tool — UR-01 mitigation verified.</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">HTTP POST to `/api/insights/assistant/query` works end-to-end against Spaarke Dev BFF — both playbook path (200 OK with `path: "playbook"`) and RAG path (200 OK with `path: "rag"`) responses parsed correctly and forwarded to the renderer. Confirmed by smoke-test traces in task notes.</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">`x-correlation-id` is generated per Assistant turn, set on every outbound request, retained in chat-agent telemetry, recoverable end-to-end in App Insights / Kusto (spec FR-17 / SC-16). Confirmed by smoke-test correlation-id trace evidence in task notes.</criterion>
